MongoDB will always use `_id` as the *primary key*, this behavior cannot be overwritten, though you can use the `_id` with values from your custom id. Though this might be confusing, it is better to use indexing on your custom id, and you don&#39;t need to use `ObjectId` for the custom index field, but can use your own custom id schema, like `UUID` or an incrementing integer value etc. though it has to be generated/incremented by you or some framework, like `JPA`

Check [Indexes][1]


----------


For Mongoose, you can do;

    new mongoose.Schema({
      customId: { type: Number, index: true }
      ...other field data
    });

with [`index: true`][2]


  [1]: https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/indexes/
  [2]: https://mongoosejs.com/docs/guide.html#indexes

